cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper deals with image recognition and topic modeling using a pre-trained CNN and LDA. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). It also involves natural language processing techniques, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of LDA for topic modeling suggests a focus on machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval and data management, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of parallelization techniques suggests a focus on multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category as well.
